## Usage

```dart
import 'package:flutter_api_bridge/flutter_api_bridge.dart';
import 'package:flutter_riverpod/flutter_riverpod.dart';
import 'package:{{ lang.package.name }}/{{ project.name.path.o }}.dart';

void main() {
  ApiClient.instance(
    baseUrl: 'https://api.example.com',
  );
}

Future<void> login(WidgetRef ref, LoginBody body) async {
  final api = {{ project.name.pascal.o }}.fromRef(ref);

  // Example:
  await api.{{ project.meta.api_version_name.camel.o }}.auth.login(body: body);
}
```

The app owns the `flutter_api_bridge` client, including base URL, tokens,
interceptors, retry behavior, and raw bridge access. The SDK receives Riverpod
`WidgetRef`, reads `apiProvider.notifier`, and provides typed DTOs, routes, features,
request methods, and response parsing.

## Bridge compatibility

This SDK depends on:

```yaml
flutter_api_bridge: ^0.1.0
flutter_riverpod: ^2.6.1
```

The consuming app should use a compatible version. To verify the resolved version:

```bash
flutter pub deps | grep flutter_api_bridge
flutter pub deps | grep flutter_riverpod
```

If there is a version conflict, align the app and SDK to the same compatible
dependency ranges.

